<p>I've written a code for the following program but the output seems to be wrong. Question: <a href="https://www.hackerrank.com/challenges/plus-minus" rel="nofollow">https://www.hackerrank.com/challenges/plus-minus</a></p>  <p>Code:</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; int main() {       int N,num,i,cp=0,cn=0,cz=0;      double fp,fn,fz;      scanf("%d",&amp;N);      for(i=0;i&lt;N;i++)      {          scanf("%d",&amp;num);          if(num&gt;0)             cp=cp+1;         else if(num==0)             cz=cz+1;         else             cn=cn+1;     }     fp=cp/N;     fn=cn/N;     fz=cz/N;     printf("%lf\n%lf\n%lf",fp,fn,fz);     return 0; } </code></pre>  <p>The Output comes as:</p>  <pre><code>0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 </code></pre>